Mentha arvensis var. piperascens

   [1448.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Lamiales:Labiatae
     Synonyms
   Common names Japanese mint
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 1448

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A herbaceous plant reaching a height of 60-100 cm.
   USES An oil is extracted from its leaves. This oil contains 60-85%
   menthol and is used in flavoring of pharmaceutical products,
   toothpastes, food products, cigarettes, and alcoholic beverages.
   GROWING PERIOD Perennial, growing for 5-6 years. COMMON NAMES Corn
   mint, Japanese mint, Field mint, Canadian mint. FURTHER INF Corn mint
   is native of Europe, Asia, and North America. It can be cultivated at
   elevations between 270-1500 m.

   Sources
   SOURCES (M. arvensis var. piperascens Malinvaud)
   Prakash V 1990 pp 49 54-55 [FER, DRA, TEXT, LIG, USE, RAIN]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 90 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 107 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Hornok L 1992 pp 196 [USE]
   Langer R 1991 pp 285-287 [TEMP, RAIN, PH, USE]

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
